Rahoton da aka fitar wannan mako ya ce, kungiyar da ake kira Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP) ta hada kai da kungiyar Musulunci ta Afghan-based ta kungiyar Islamic State.
Wasu daga manyan jama'ar TTP sun kuma shiga al'ummar IS, wanda yake da gidansa a yankin Arewacin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afgan ba ta amsa kiran da Associated Press ta yi a ranar Lahadi ba.
Rahoton ya ce IS a Afaganistan, wanda aka sani da IS a yankin Khorasan, ya samu rauni mai tsanani daga kungiyoyin tsaro na Afaganistan da kuma kungiyoyin Amurka da NATO, har ma da lokutan da taliban Afagan suka yi.
U.N. ta kiyasta rahoton ta hanyar kungiyar binciken da ta kula da hana ayyuka na ta'addanci a duniya.
Rahoton ya yi kiyasin yawan jama'ar IS a Afghanistan a 2,200, kuma yayin da shugabancinsa ya yi yawa, IS har yanzu yana daga cikin shugabanninsa wani mutumin Syria Abu Said Mohammad al-Khorasani.
Rahoton ya ce kuma, jami'ar binciken ta samu labarin cewa biyu daga cikin masu ruwa da tsaki na kungiyar IS, Abu Qutaibah da Abu Hajar al-Iraqi, sun zo Afghanistan daga Tsakiyar Turai da makonni biyu da suka wuce.
Duk da cewa a yanzu an yi musu kasa da kasa, (Jamhuriyar Musulunci) har yanzu ta iya aikata muhimman ayyuka a cikin yankunan daban-daban na kasar, ciki har da Kabul.
An kuma yana nufin ya kasance ya kara jin dadin makiyaya Taliban da suka yi wa karar da aka yi da Amurka, kamar yadda rahoton ya ce, wanda ya nuna zuwa ga yarjejeniyar zaman lafiya da Amurka ta yi da Taliban a watan Fabrairu.
Wannan yarjejeniya ta samo asali don yin saukar da Amurka daga halin da take ciki na shekaru 19 a Afghanistan, kuma ta kira ga Taliban su tabbatar da cewa babban yankin da suke da shi ba zai zama wuri ga kungiyoyin terorist ba.
Aikace-aikacen ya kuma zai tabbatar da halartar Taliban gaba daya a cikin yakin da ake yi da IS.
Tsakanin Taliban da jagorancin siyasa na Kabul ya kamata a yi magana, wannan shi ne muhimmin sashi na biyu na yarjejeniyar.
Ranar Asabar da ta gabata, Ma'aikatar Tsaro ta Amurka ta fitar da wata sanarwa cewa tawagar zaman lafiya ta ta, Zalmay Khalilzad, ta sake yin tafiya a yankin don fara wannan tattaunawa da aka sake kara lokuta, wadanda aka yi kaurin suna a kan shirin saki 'yan tawaye da aka yi.
Aikace-aikacen da Amurka ta bayarwa ya nema gwamnatin Afghan ta saki 5,000 daga cikin 'yan taliban da kuma 'yan taliban su saki 1,000 daga cikin ma'aikatan gwamnati da kuma 'yan sanda a matsayin alama ta kyauta kafin su fara tattaunawa.
Har yanzu gwamnatin ta ki sakin 'yan Taliban dari 600 da take kira masu laifi muhimmanci, kuma ta bayar da zaɓuɓɓuka don sakin su.
Talibai sun ki karba.
An sanar da Ofishin Shugabancin Amurka cewa, "Dangantakar tsakanin al'ummomi sun fi kusa da fara tattaunawa tsakanin al'ummomi a Afaganistan, wanda shine matakin gaba na karewa da yakin da Afaganistan ke fama da shi na shekaru 40."
Duk da ci gaba mai yawa ya samu a kan hanyoyin sakin jama'a, an bukaci aiki mai yawa don cimma matsayin gaba daya.
Spokesman ƙungiyar siyasa Taliban a ranar Litinin da ta gabata ya ce suna shirin yin magana da jagororin siyasar Kabul bayan kwanakin bikin musulunci na Eid al-Adha a ƙarshen wannan watan, in an gama da saki mutane daga hannunsu.
Babban damuwa ga Pakistan shi ne yawan makamai a Afghanistan, musamman waɗanda ke da alaka da TTP ko Jamaat-ul-Ahrar ko Lashkar-e-Islam, har ma da waɗanda ke da alaka da Baluchistan Liberation Army, wanda ya dauki alhakin yawan masu garkuwa da mutane a watan wannan a yankin Sindh ta kudu da kuma yankin Baluchistan ta yamma.
Wataƙila 'yan sanda na Pakistan sun mutu a wannan wata a yankin Kudancin Baluchistan yayin da suke yaki da masu yaki.
TTP ta dauki alhakin wani daga cikin mafi munin makamai a Pakistan a 2014, lokacin da makarantar sojojin Pakistan ta kashe kuma 140 suka mutu.
Yawancin su ne dalibai, kuma wasu kamar yara har 5.
Rahoton ya ce, an kiyasta cewa, akwai tsakanin 6,000 zuwa 6,500 na 'yan ta'addan makiyaya na Pakistan a Afghanistan, wadanda suke haifar da kalubale ga kasashen biyu, kuma mafi yawan su suna da alaka da TTP.
Bankin Biritaniya mafi girma HSBC ta musanta cewa ta "sanya hanyar karewa" ga binciken Amurka na Huawei - RT Business News
Bankin kasar Ingila mai suna HSBC da ke tsaye a birnin London ya yi amfani da sada zumunta don bayyana cewa ba shi ba, kamar yadda jaridar kasar Sin ta bayyana, ya "tsara bayanai" a kan Huawei wanda ya haifar da kama mataimakin shugaban kudin kamfanin a kasar Kanada ba.
A cikin wani post da ba za a samu a yanzu a kan WeChat, mai bashi ya ce cewa ayyukansa ba su tashi US bincike game da mafi girma samarwa na tsarin wayar tarho a duniya, saboda binciken Huawei na zargin ta ta karya dokar US akan Iran ya fara kafin shiga bankin a karshen shekara ta 2016.
Bankin HSBC ba ya da wata kishin Huawei ba, kuma ba ya "tsara" Huawei ba, bankin ya ce a Asabar, kuma ya kara da cewa ba zai taba sanya wa abokan ciniki nasa karya ba.
A gabanin bukatar DOJ ta Amurka na bayanai, HSBC Group kawai ta bayar da bayanai masu gaskiya.
HSBC ba ta "tsara" shaidar ko ta "sakaya" al'amuran ba.
Kuma akan rt.com UK ya yanke shawarar kashe Huawei daga tsarin 5G yana nuna US ta yanke shawarar yada siyasa ta waje ta Birtaniya - George Galloway zuwa Boom Bust
An rufe shafin da aka yi da wata rubutu cewa "Yana karya dokoki" kuma ba za a samu shi yanzu ba.
Bayanin ya zo nan da nan bayan da jaridun kasar Sin da ke da alaka da gwamnati, suka zargi HSBC da "haduwa" da Washington don yin wani hannun da zai kama Huawei.
Kamfanin ya zama a cikin wani rikici na siyasa na fiye da shekara daya da rabi tun lokacin da Mataimakin Shugaban Huawei Meng Wanzhou ta yi kama a watan Disamba 2018 a Kanada a kan umarnin daga Amurka.
Meng ya fuskanci tuhuma na zalunci saboda an tuhume shi da amfani da kamfanin kwari don karya dokokin da suka shafi Iran, kuma an tuhume shi da yin karya ga bankuna game da alaka tsakanin Huawei da kamfanin Iran Skycom.
Bayanai da sabuwar hujja da Global Times ta bayar, HSBC ya san cikakken alaka tsakanin kamfanin Sin da Skycom.
Bankin ya bayyana zai yi "hadama" da gwamnatin Amurka don tsira daga hukunci mafi tsanani a shekarar 2012, lokacin da bankin ya yi amfani da laundar kudi da laifin yin laifi, ciki har da kiyayewa kan Iran.
